      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">9.306</ph> Solicitation requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Solicitations containing a testing and approval requirement
shall-</p>
         <ol id="d571e16" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e20" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Provide,
in the circumstance where the contractor is to be responsible for
the first article approval testing-</p>
               <ol id="d571e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The performance
or other characteristics that the first article must meet for approval;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The detailed
technical requirements for the tests that must be performed for
approval; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e48" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> The necessary
data that must be submitted to the Government in the first article
approval <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 9.306 by—  a.  Removing from paragraph (a)(3) “test report.” and adding “test report;” in its place;?>test <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>report;</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e65" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Provide,
in the circumstance where the Government is to be responsible for
the first article approval testing-</p>
               <ol id="d571e65" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The performance
or other characteristics that the first article must meet for approval;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The tests
to which the first article will be subjected <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Removing from paragraph (b)(2) “for approval.” and adding “for approval;” in its place;?>for <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>approval;</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e101" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Inform
offerors that the requirement may be waived when supplies identical
or similar to those called for have previously been delivered by
the offeror and accepted by the Government <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] c.  Removing from paragraph (c) “(see 52.209-3(h) and 52.209-4(i);” and adding “(see 52.209-3(h) and 52.209-4(i));” in its place?>(see <xref href="FAR-i1062501.dita#i1062501"
                           base="i1062501"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">52.209-3</xref>(h) <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>and <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                           base="i1062528"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>(i))</ph>;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e122" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> Permit
the submission of alternative offers, one including testing and
approval and the other excluding testing and approval (if eligible
under <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] d.  Removing from paragraph (d) “9.306(c)” and adding “paragraph (c) of this section” in its place;?>paragraph (c) of this
section);<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendment?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e136" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph> State clearly
the first article’s relationship to the contract quantity (see paragraph
(e) of the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1062501.dita#i1062501"
                        base="i1062501"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-3</xref>,
First Article Approval-Contractor Testing, or <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                        base="i1062528"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>, First Article
Approval-Government Testing);</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e152" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph> Contain
a delivery schedule for the production quantity <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] e. Removing from paragraph (f) “quantity (see 11.404)” and adding “quantity (see 11.403)” in its place;?>(see<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?><xref href="FAR-id1617MD00RFX.dita#id1617MD00RFX"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">11.403</xref>)</ph>. The delivery
schedule may-</p>
               <ol id="d571e138" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e171" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Be the same whether or not testing
and approval is waived; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e180" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Provide
for earlier delivery when testing and approval is waived and the
Government desires earlier delivery. In the latter case, any resulting
difference in delivery schedules shall not be a factor in evaluation
for award. The clause at <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                              base="i1062528"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>,
First Article Approval-Government Testing, shall contain the delivery
schedule for the first article;</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e194" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph> Provide
for the submission of contract numbers, if any, to document the
offeror’s eligibility under <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] f.  Removing from paragraph (g) “9.306(c)” and adding “paragraph (c) of this section” in its place;?>paragraph
(c) of this section;<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendment?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e208" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph> State whether
the approved first article will serve as a manufacturing <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] e.  Removing from paragraph (h) “and”; and?>standard;<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e222" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Include,
when the Government is responsible for first article testing, the
Government’s estimated testing costs as a factor for use in evaluating
offers <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 May 6, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">(when <?FM MARKER [Why] h.  Removing from paragraph (i) “(when appropriate).” and adding “(when appropriate); and” in its place.?>appropriate); <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>and</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e238" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(j)</ph> Inform
offerors that the prices for first articles and first article tests
in relation to production quantities shall not be materially unbalanced
(see <xref href="FAR-i1106135.dita#i1106135"
                        base="i1106135"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.404-1</xref>(g)) if first
article test items or tests are to be separately priced.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
